ABOUT BOYS UNDER 60.

03:15.025 --> 03:17.487
OKAY, THAT'S AN
IMAGE I DON'T NEED,

03:17.488 --> 03:20.580
BUT I'M ALL EARS.

03:20.581 --> 03:23.743
WELL, I TEXTED THIS BOY,
ABOUT, YOU KNOW, HANGING OUT,

03:23.744 --> 03:24.994
AND HE HASN'T TEXT ME BACK.

03:24.995 --> 03:27.957
SO WHEN I TEXT HIM AGAIN,
WHAT SHOULD I SAY?

03:27.958 --> 03:29.249
DON'T SAY ANYTHING,

03:29.250 --> 03:31.000
BECAUSE YOU DON'T WANT TO
LOOK LIKE A DESPERATE FREAK,

03:31.001 --> 03:33.423
AND THERE'S NO RECOVERING
FROM THE DOUBLE TEXT.

03:33.424 --> 03:37.837
- HOW DO YOU KNOW?
- IT HAPPENED TO ME.

03:37.838 --> 03:40.009
IT WAS A LONG TIME AGO.

03:40.010 --> 03:42.722
IT WAS A FLIP PHONE.

03:42.723 --> 03:44.725
A WHAT?

03:49.149 --> 03:50.980
CAN WE PLUG IT IN NOW?

03:50.981 --> 03:53.983
NO, IT'S ONLY BEEN TWO MINUTES
AND 17 SECONDS. OKAY?

03:53.984 --> 03:55.905
THE BAROMETRIC PRESSURE IS 29.9.

03:55.906 --> 03:59.739
OH, AND IT'S ALMOST LUNCHTIME IN JAKARTA.
(laughs) I LOVE MY WATCH.

03:59.740 --> 04:01.821
GUESS WHAT?

04:01.822 --> 04:04.073
DANI JUST CAME TO ME FOR
ADVICE, AND I GAVE IT TO HER.

04:04.074 --> 04:06.866
AH! NOW I KNOW THE SATISFACTION
YOU FEEL WHEN YOU GIVE ME ADVICE.

04:06.867 --> 04:09.919
OH, HONEY, I DON'T GIVE YOU ADVICE
FOR THE FEELING OF SATISFACTION.

04:09.920 --> 04:12.332
I GIVE IT TO YOU FOR THE
FEELING OF SUPERIORITY.

04:12.333 --> 04:14.754
NO, YOU KNOW, IT'S JUST FOR
THE FIRST TIME I FEEL LIKE

04:14.755 --> 04:16.966
I KNOW WHAT IT MEANS TO
HAVE A LITTLE SISTER.

04:16.967 --> 04:18.468
OH! THIS IS SO WONDERFUL!

04:18.469 --> 04:21.090
I HAVE MENTORED YOU
INTO BECOMING A MENTOR!

04:21.091 --> 04:25.014
WOW. HOW DID YOU MANAGE TO MAKE
THIS ABOUT YOU SO QUICKLY?

04:25.015 --> 04:26.766
SOMEDAY, I'LL TEACH YOU.

04:26.767 --> 04:29.018
- HOW ABOUT NOW?
- THIS IS NOT A TOASTER, HONEY.

04:29.019 --> 04:31.891
ALL RIGHT? THIS IS A PRECISION
PIECE OF ELECTRONIC EQUIPMENT.

04:31.892 --> 04:33.653
OKAY. ALL RIGHT, READY?

04:33.654 --> 04:37.157
SIX, FIVE, FOUR, THREE...

04:38.899 --> 04:40.109
CLOSE ENOUGH.

04:40.110 --> 04:43.242
- OH! OKAY. HERE WE GO.
- (computer chimes)

04:43.243 --> 04:46.536
AND THE INTERNET IS BACK TO FULL...
TRICKLE. WHAT?

04:46.537 --> 04:48.408
I DON'T GET IT!

04:48.409 --> 04:50.580
WELL, YOU DID
EVERYTHING YOU COULD.

04:50.581 --> 04:52.912
I MEAN, NO ONE COULD
HAVE DONE ANY MORE.

04:52.913 --> 04:54.964
EXCEPT MAYBE A PROFESSIONAL,
WHICH IS WHY I THINK

04:54.965 --> 04:57.297
IT WOULDN'T BE A BAD THING
RIGHT NOW TO CALL JIFFY NERDS.

04:59.840 --> 05:01.591
THE GUYS IN THE
ORANGE SMART CARS?

05:01.592 --> 05:04.924
THEY'RE PROFESSIONAL NERDS, ANY CAR
THEY GET IN IS GONNA BE SMART.

05:04.925 --> 05:06.516
I CAN FIX THIS MYSELF, MEL.

05:06.517 --> 05:10.189
JOE, DARLING, TENDER
JOE, I LOVE YOU.

05:10.190 --> 05:13.984
AND EVEN IF YOU CAN'T FIX EVERYTHING
IN THE HOUSE, I WILL STILL LOVE YOU.

05:16.857 --> 05:19.439
THAT IS THE CRUELEST THING
YOU'VE EVER SAID TO ME.

05:19.440 --> 05:21.571
OH, HEY, YOU GUYS,
I JUST TEXT RYDER.

05:21.572 --> 05:23.903
AND HE'S GOING OUT WITH HIS FRIENDS
LATER, BUT HE'S HOME RIGHT NOW.

05:23.904 --> 05:25.865
SO WE CAN JUST TEXT
HIM "HAPPY BIRTHDAY."

05:25.866 --> 05:27.997
LENNOX, DO NOT GO THERE.

05:27.998 --> 05:30.249
