HAVING A LITTLE SISTER

10:24.044 --> 10:26.956
WAS WHEN RYDER WENT
THROUGH HIS BRONY PHASE.

10:26.957 --> 10:29.588
SO I WANTED TO SAY THAT I
THINK IT'S PRETTY COOL

10:29.589 --> 10:32.802
THAT YOU CAME TO ME FOR SOME "BIG
SISTER TO LITTLE SISTER" ADVICE.

10:32.803 --> 10:34.423
YEMM...

10:34.424 --> 10:36.635
AND I THINK IT WAS
PRETTY GOOD ADVICE.

10:36.636 --> 10:38.217
YOU KNOW, ABOUT NOT
TEXTING THAT BOY.

10:38.218 --> 10:39.598
MM-HM.

10:39.599 --> 10:40.930
WAIT, ARE YOU TEXTING THAT BOY?

10:40.931 --> 10:42.351
- I SAID NO DOUBLE TEXTING!
- NO!

10:42.352 --> 10:43.602
- NO, GIVE ME THE PHONE!
- NO!

10:43.603 --> 10:44.974
- LET...
- LADIES!

10:44.975 --> 10:45.816
TAKE YOUR PILLOW FIGHT UPSTAIRS!

10:45.817 --> 10:47.146
I HAVE A TICKING CLOCK HERE!

10:47.147 --> 10:49.318
- GET...
- OH!

10:49.319 --> 10:52.271
(gasps) "JOSHNIBBLING."
I KNEW IT!

10:52.272 --> 10:55.905
YOU KNOW WHAT? I'M KEEPING THIS UNTIL
YOUR CRAZY TEXTING URGE PASSES.

10:55.906 --> 10:57.576
OKAY, YOU'RE RIGHT.

10:57.577 --> 11:00.119
IF IT MAKES YOU FEEL ANY BETTER
I DIDN'T EVEN HIT "SEND."

11:00.120 --> 11:02.411
SO CAN I PLEASE
HAVE MY PHONE BACK?

11:02.412 --> 11:06.455
I SWEAR TO YOU I
WILL NOT TEXT HIM.

11:06.456 --> 11:10.050
LITTLE SISTER TO BIG SISTER?

11:11.842 --> 11:15.134
OH, "LITTLE SISTER TO BIG
SISTER." I LIKE THAT.

11:15.135 --> 11:16.635
YOUR SOCIAL LIFE WILL THANK ME.

11:16.636 --> 11:19.008
AND "SEND."

11:19.009 --> 11:21.430
YOU SWORE!

11:21.431 --> 11:23.182
HOW ELSE WAS I SUPPOSED
TO GET MY PHONE BACK?

11:23.183 --> 11:25.014
OKAY, YOU KNOW WHAT?

11:25.015 --> 11:26.806
THE NEXT TIME YOU WANT
TO ASK ME FOR ADVICE,

11:26.807 --> 11:30.810
HERE'S SOME ADVICE. DON'T.

11:30.811 --> 11:33.612
I THOUGHT ABOUT WHAT
YOU SAID, HONEST.

11:33.613 --> 11:35.945
I JUST DON'T THINK IT APPLIES
TO KIDS FROM MY GENERATION.

11:35.946 --> 11:37.778
IT'S FINE FOR OLDER
FOLKS LIKE YOU.

11:40.370 --> 11:41.620
I'M 20!

11:41.621 --> 11:43.914
UH, YEAH?

11:45.996 --> 11:48.667
(groans) I'VE NEVER
BEEN CALLED OLD BEFORE.

11:48.668 --> 11:51.670
OH, NOW I KNOW HOW
AUNT MEL FEELS.

11:51.671 --> 11:55.634
- (phone chimes)
- IT'S JOSH!

11:55.635 --> 11:57.927
"SORRY, I MEANT TO GET
BACK TO YOU SOONER.

11:57.928 --> 12:01.470
THANKS FOR REMINDING ME.
SEE YOU AT THE PARTY."

12:01.471 --> 12:04.053
LENNOX, YOUR ADVICE WAS USEFUL.

12:04.054 --> 12:06.685
SOMETIMES A PERSON NEEDS
TO HEAR THE WRONG THING

12:06.686 --> 12:08.849
IN ORDER TO KNOW
THE RIGHT THING.

12:11.061 --> 12:14.274
YEAH, I GUESS THAT'S WHAT
OLDER SISTERS ARE FOR.

12:16.656 --> 12:19.158
- (computer beeps)
- YES! YEP! I'M A HERO!

12:19.159 --> 12:21.070
DANI, GET OVER HERE!
LOOK AT THIS!

12:21.071 --> 12:23.122
I REINSTALLED THE O.S., UPDATED
THE VIDEO CHAT SOFTWARE,

12:23.123 --> 12:24.864
AND NOW WE DON'T HAVE TO
WORRY ABOUT THE WIFI ANYMORE

12:24.865 --> 12:28.788
BECAUSE I JUST HARD-WIRED THE
COMPUTER TO THE ROUTER. HUH? AWESOME.

12:28.789 --> 12:32.711
- OH, BOY! CAN I GO NOW?
- YES. YES, YOU CAN, HONEY.

12:32.712 --> 12:34.874
TO THE KITCHEN. ALL RIGHT? GO TELL
MEL AND LENNOX WE ARE SECONDS AWAY

12:34.875 --> 12:38.138
FROM CONNECTING WITH RYDER AND WISHING HIM
A GLITCH-FREE VIRTUAL HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

12:39.139 --> 12:42.301
OH! NO! OH!

12:42.302 --> 12:46.385
I'M SORRY! I'M SORRY! CURSE
THESE WILD COLTISH LEGS!

12:46.386 --> 12:48.387
PLEASE DON'T BE MAD!

12:48.388 --> 12:51.691
MAD, ME? (chuckles)

12:52.983 --> 12:55.234
SINCE I'M SORT OF
RESPONSIBLE FOR THIS...

12:55.235 --> 12:58.948
YOU KNOW, HONEY, I DON'T THINK YOU'RE
USING "SORT OF" THE RIGHT WAY.

12:58.949 --> 13:02.361
I CAN MAKE IT RIGHT. COME ON.

13:02.362 --> 13:04.113
- WHERE ARE WE GOING?
- UPSTAIRS.

13:04.114 --> 13:06.826
- WHAT'S UPSTAIRS?
- NEIGHBOR'S WIFI.

13:06.827 --> 13:08.748
THE NEIGH... WHAT?

13:09.910 --> 13:11.080
OKAY, ALL WE NEED TO DO

13:11.081 --> 13:13.372
IS MAKE A PERISCOPE OUT OF
PAPER TOWEL ROLLS AND MIRRORS.

13:13.373 --> 13:15.464
THEN YOU CAN PEEK AT MY HUSBAND'S
COMPUTER THROUGH THE WINDOW.

13:15.465 --> 13:17.256
COME ON, YOU'RE A
NERD, IT'LL BE EASY.

13:17.257 --> 13:19.678
I NEED TO BE AT THE
COMPUTER, TOUCHING IT.

13:19.679 --> 13:22.842
- CAN'T I GO INSIDE? -NO, NO, NO! MY
HUSBAND DOESN'T KNOW I CALLED YOU.

13:22.843 --> 13:26.135
CAN'T YOU DO SOMETHING WITHOUT
HAVING THE ACTUAL COMPUTER?

13:26.136 --> 13:29.018
WELL, I GUESS I COULD CHECK IF
THE TROUBLE IS ON THE OTHER END.

13:29.019 --> 13:32.351
YES! ON THE OTHER END! NOW
YOU'RE THINKING LIKE A NERD!

13:32.352 --> 13:35.024
(blows)

13:35.025 --> 13:37.606
OH! WELL, HERE YOU GO.
HERE'S YOUR TROUBLE.

13:37.607 --> 13:39.738
YOU HAVE NO WIFI SIGNAL.

13:39.739 --> 13:42.992
I'LL GET MY HOTSPOT OUT OF THE JIFFYMOBILE.
BE RIGHT BACK.

13:42.993 --> 13:44.323
GO, 14 MINUTES!

13:44.324 --> 13:46.406
RUN, YOU GLORIOUS NERD, RUN!

13:54.004 --> 13:58.127
YES! FOUR BARS. THANK YOU, MR.
AND MRS. BUCHWALD.

13:58.128 --> 14:01.050
I'LL JUST ENTER THEIR PASSWORD.

14:01.051 --> 14:02.221
(computer chimes)

14:02.222 --> 14:03.552
WHAT?! THEY CHANGED IT!

14:03.553 --> 14:06.305
DOESN'T ANYONE TRUST
THEIR NEIGHBORS ANYMORE?

14:06.306 --> 14:10.429
- WHAT WAS THE OLD PASSWORD?
- THEIR CAT'S NAME: MR. CUTIE PIE.

14:10.430 --> 14:11.811
YOU KNOW, I HATE THAT CAT.

14:12.933 --> 14:14.023
HEY, THEY HAVE KIDS.

14:14.024 --> 14:15.644
- WHAT ABOUT THEIR NAMES?
- OH, OKAY.

14:15.645 --> 14:17.066
UH, YEAH, YEAH, YEAH. UM...

14:17.067 --> 14:19.899
THE, UH... CHUBBY ONE.

14:19.900 --> 14:21.440
UH, "FOOD IN THE HAIR."

14:21.441 --> 14:24.613
AND, UH, "THE ONE WHO'S ALWAYS
GOT HIS HANDS IN HIS PANTS."

14:24.614 --> 14:26.986
IS THAT ALL CAPS
OR ALL LOWERCASE?

14:26.987 --> 14:28.788
I'M DOING MY BEST HERE!

14:30.660 --> 14:32.041
GETTING A CONNECTION
WITH YOUR NEPHEW.

14:32.042 --> 14:33.252
OKAY. REMEMBER, THIS
IS JUST A TEST.

14:33.253 --> 14:34.833
NO BIRTHDAY STUFF, NO SINGING.

14:34.834 --> 14:36.795
IN FACT, YOU KNOW WHAT? RYDER
SHOULDN'T SEE ME AT ALL.

14:36.796 --> 14:38.918
HE'LL FEEL BAD IF IT'S
NOT ALL OF US TOGETHER.

14:38.919 --> 14:39.919
Ryder: Hey, it's Ryder.

14:39.920 --> 14:42.001
Do I know you?

14:42.002 --> 14:44.383
JIFFY NERD. JUST TESTING
THE CONNECTION.

14:44.384 --> 14:47.967
- Yeah. -HEY, WEREN'T YOU THE GAME
MASTER AT THAT LASER TAG PLACE?

14:47.968 --> 14:50.639
HEY, YEAH, I KNOW YOU. YOU WERE
THE GUY THAT USED TO COME IN

14:50.640 --> 14:52.561
ALL THE TIME WITH
THE REALLY HOT MOM.

14:52.562 --> 14:54.813
- YEAH, MAN! GOOD TO SEE YOU.
- Dani: AUNT MEL!

14:54.814 --> 14:56.895
I'VE OUTLIVED MY USEFULNESS.

14:56.896 --> 14:58.227
OH, YOU POOR THING.

14:58.228 --> 15:00.070
TELL ME EVERYTHING.
SOMEWHERE ELSE.

15:01.611 --> 15:03.732
OKAY. I'M ALL EARS.

15:03.733 --> 15:05.824
TALK. QUICKLY.

15:05.825 --> 15:08.287
OKAY, WELL, I THOUGHT I WAS
BEING A BIG SISTER TO DANI

15:08.288 --> 15:10.789
BY GIVING HER WHAT I HUMBLY
WOULD CONSIDER GREAT ADVICE,

15:10.790 --> 15:13.202
BUT THEN SHE JUST GOES
AND DOES THE OPPOSITE.

15:13.203 --> 15:15.624
OH, SWEETIE. QUICKER.

15:15.625 --> 15:17.296
WELL, SHE CONSIDERS ME A RELIC.

15:17.297 --> 15:20.170
YOU KNOW, AT 20 YEARS OLD I
HAVE NOTHING MORE TO OFFER.

15:21.631 --> 15:23.132
OH, I'M LIKE ONE OF
THOSE OLD LADIES

15:23.133 --> 15:25.214
THAT USED TO COME TO OUR
SCHOOL AND TALK ABOUT SMOKING.

15:25.215 --> 15:27.846
OH, THERE, THERE.

15:27.847 --> 15:31.390
- BETTER? -SERIOUSLY? THAT'S ALL I GET?
"THERE, THERE"?

15:31.391 --> 15:33.812
SOMETIMES THAT'S ENOUGH. OKAY?

15:33.813 --> 15:36.725
NOW I THINK YOU SHOULD GO TO
YOUR ROOM AND THINK ABOUT THIS.

15:36.726 --> 15:38.267
YEAH, "THERE, THERE." OH!

15:38.268 --> 15:40.609
YOU'LL SEE. IT'S LIKE
A TIME-RELEASE THING.

15:40.610 --> 15:41.901
OKAY? GO.

15:43.984 --> 15:47.276
WHY WOULD YOU GIVE UP A JOB WHERE YOU
CAN PLAY ENDLESS FREE LASER TAG?

15:47.277 --> 15:49.198
I wanted to do
something meaningful.

15:49.199 --> 15:52.911
I volunteered for AmeriCorps.

15:52.912 --> 15:54.743
No, seriously, I just
followed a hot girl.

15:54.744 --> 15:57.956
HEY, I'M NOT PAYING YOU A HUNDRED
DOLLARS TO GAB! HANG UP!

15:57.957 --> 16:00.169
UH, GOTTA GO, DUDE.
GREAT CATCHING UP.

16:00.170 --> 16:03.582
Later. Thanks for calling me on my
birthday. You were the only one.

16:03.583 --> 16:05.844
OKAY, IT'S NOT YOUR WIFI.

16:05.845 --> 16:07.426
SO THEN THAT MEANS...

16:07.427 --> 16:09.468
IT MEANS, I SWEAR, IF
YOU JUST LET ME HOLD

16:09.469 --> 16:11.930
THE BROKEN COMPUTER, I CAN
FIX IT IN FIVE MINUTES.

16:11.931 --> 16:14.643
OKAY. I JUST HAVE TO
DISTRACT MY HUSBAND.

16:14.644 --> 16:17.476
UM... OOH, I'LL JUST TAKE HIM UPSTAIRS
FOR A QUICKIE. OKAY WITH YOU?

16:17.477 --> 16:20.149
ACTUALLY, YOU'RE GROSSING ME
OUT, BUT ANYTHING TO GET INSIDE.

16:20.150 --> 16:22.861
OKAY, COME ON.

16:22.862 --> 16:24.363
OKAY, SO MR. BUCHWALD
IS A SPORTS NUT,

16:24.364 --> 16:26.985
SO IF IT'S NOT "GO
BENGALS" OR "GO INDIANS,"

16:26.986 --> 16:28.867
THEN IT'S GOTTA BE, UM...

16:28.868 --> 16:30.819
OOH! "GO CAVALIERS."

16:30.820 --> 16:32.071
- (computer chimes)
- WE'RE IN!

16:32.072 --> 16:35.574
- WAS I RIGHT? -OH, I WASN'T LISTENING.
I HAD MY OWN IDEA.

16:35.575 --> 16:38.497
(laughs) GUESS WHAT THE
BUCHWALD'S WIFI PASSWORD IS.

16:38.498 --> 16:41.541
- WHAT?
- "BUCHWALDWIFI."

16:43.923 --> 16:45.964
SO, DAUGHTER, WE DID IT!

16:45.965 --> 16:48.257
ACTUALLY, I DID IT.

16:48.258 --> 16:50.469
YOU KNOW, HONEY, JUST A
LITTLE LIFE LESSON HERE:

16:50.470 --> 16:53.092
WHEN YOU HAVE A VICTORY, IT'S
NICE TO SPREAD THE JOY AROUND.

16:53.093 --> 16:54.843
ESPECIALLY WITH THE PERSON
WHO PAYS YOUR ALLOWANCE.

16:54.844 --> 16:57.806
- GOT IT.
- GOT IT. OKAY.

16:57.807 --> 17:00.018
AND WITH FIVE MINUTES TO SPARE,
I'M GONNA GO TELL MEL AND LENNOX

17:00.019 --> 17:02.901
WE'RE GONNA MAKE
THAT BIRTHDAY CALL.

17:02.902 --> 17:06.024
OKAY, LOOK, WHILE I AM UPSTAIRS
WORKING MY MAGIC ON MY HUSBAND,

17:06.025 --> 17:08.107
YOU NEED TO BE DOWNSTAIRS WORKING
YOUR MAGIC ON THE COMPUTER.

17:08.108 --> 17:10.239
BUT, YOU KNOW, NOT THE
SAME KIND OF MAGIC.

17:10.240 --> 17:14.073
WOULDN'T IT BE EASIER IF YOU JUST
USED MY COMPUTER TO MAKE THE CALL?

17:14.074 --> 17:15.455
MY HUSBAND CANNOT
KNOW YOU'RE HERE!

17:16.866 --> 17:18.497
WHO THE HELL IS THIS?

17:18.498 --> 17:20.539
UH... JOE,

17:20.540 --> 17:24.253
I... I CAN'T KEEP THIS
A SECRET ANY LONGER!

17:24.254 --> 17:25.795
THIS IS MY LOVER!

17:28.798 --> 17:32.381
YOUR LOVER, HUH? WHO CONVENIENTLY
JUST HAPPENS TO FIX COMPUTERS?

17:32.382 --> 17:36.095
WELL, UH, I GOT SICK OF THE MUSCLE-Y,
HUNKY TYPE, AND DECIDED TO CHANGE IT UP.

17:36.096 --> 17:38.978
- YOU KNOW, TRY ME SOME SCRAWNY.
- HEY!

17:40.230 --> 17:43.852
FINE, I CALLED A JIFFY NERD.

17:43.853 --> 17:45.604
FLASH, JOE. JOE, FLASH.

17:45.605 --> 17:48.357
I'VE BEEN IN THE MIDDLE OF
THIS ARGUMENT TOO MANY TIMES.

17:48.358 --> 17:50.819
MY THERAPIST SAYS IT'S
WHY I CAN NEVER LOVE.

17:50.820 --> 17:53.992
SO IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME...

17:53.993 --> 17:55.995
YOUR BILL IS IN YOUR INBOX.

17:57.247 --> 17:58.957
I TOLD YOU I WAS GONNA
FIX THE INTERNET,

17:58.958 --> 18:01.910
AND I FIXED THE INTERNET. WHAT
HAPPENED TO THE HONESTY HERE?

18:01.911 --> 18:04.703
THERE'S NO TIME FOR HONESTY. WE ONLY HAVE
FOUR MINUTES TILL WE HAVE TO CALL RYDER.

18:04.704 --> 18:06.585
SO IT'S OKAY TO LIE BEHIND
MY BACK AS LONG AS RYDER

18:06.586 --> 18:08.006
GETS HIS BIRTHDAY
CALL BEFORE MIDNIGHT?

18:08.007 --> 18:09.798
SEE? I KNEW YOU'D UNDERSTAND.

18:09.799 --> 18:13.011
HEY, ARE WE CALLING
RYDER OR NOT?

18:13.012 --> 18:15.013
NO, I DON'T REALLY FEEL LIKE SINGING.
YOU GUYS GO AHEAD.

18:15.014 --> 18:17.015
WHAT? NO! WE ALL HAVE TO
SING OR IT DOESN'T COUNT!

18:17.016 --> 18:19.808
MEL, WHY... WHY IS THIS
SO IMPORTANT TO YOU?

18:19.809 --> 18:22.561
DO YOU WANT RYDER TO BE
HURT AND UPSET ABOUT THIS

18:22.562 --> 18:26.185
FOR YEARS AND YEARS TO COME,
UNTIL HE'S A GROWN WOMAN?

18:26.186 --> 18:28.397
OKAY, I THINK WE'RE ONTO SOMETHING HERE.
NOBODY MOVE.

18:28.398 --> 18:32.861
MY WHOLE LIFE MY FATHER WAS
NEVER THERE FOR MY BIRTHDAY.

18:32.862 --> 18:35.324
YOU KNOW, IT JUST FELT LIKE THAT
DAY JUST WASN'T IMPORTANT TO HIM.

18:35.325 --> 18:39.448
BUT FOR MY SIXTEENTH BIRTHDAY
HE SWORE HE WOULD BE THERE.

18:39.449 --> 18:42.581
SO WE HAD A BIG PARTY,
AND HE DIDN'T SHOW UP.

18:42.582 --> 18:45.794
AND I WAS STANDING THERE IN
A ROOM FULL OF MY FRIENDS

18:45.795 --> 18:48.046
IN MY BEAUTIFUL PINK
STRAPLESS DRESS

18:48.047 --> 18:51.009
WITH TEARS AND MASCARA
STREAMING DOWN MY FACE,

18:51.010 --> 18:53.802
AND I JUST DON'T WANT
THAT TO HAPPEN TO RYDER!

18:53.803 --> 18:57.136
BELIEVE ME, I DON'T WANT
THAT TO HAPPEN RYDER EITHER.

18:58.888 --> 19:01.930
ALL RIGHT, WE'RE SINGING
HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO THE BOY.

19:01.931 --> 19:04.644
TO THE NEIGHBORS' WIFI! COME ON.

19:05.935 --> 19:07.065
IT'S TWO MINUTES TO MIDNIGHT!

19:07.066 --> 19:08.647
- DIAL IT!
- NO, WAIT, WAIT!

19:08.648 --> 19:10.899
WE HAVEN'T REHEARSED THE SPECIAL
BIRTHDAY SONG SINCE YESTERDAY.

19:10.900 --> 19:13.111
- COME ON, ONE PRACTICE ROUND.
- LENNOX, WHAT'S BETTER,

19:13.112 --> 19:14.943
SINGING THE VERSES TOGETHER
OR DIVIDING IT UP?

19:14.944 --> 19:17.075
OH, SUDDENLY YOU WANT
GRANDMA'S ADVICE?

19:17.076 --> 19:18.617
LET ME TELL YOU
SOMETHING, MISSY:

19:18.618 --> 19:21.330
BACK IN MY DAY, WE
ALL SANG TOGETHER.

19:21.331 --> 19:24.663
- ALL RIGHT. READY?
- OKAY.

19:24.664 --> 19:26.955
♪ HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO YOU ♪

19:26.956 --> 19:28.837
♪ HAPPY BIRTHDAY, RYDER ♪

19:28.838 --> 19:31.290
♪ WE'RE SENDING YOU
A LOT OF LOVE ♪

19:31.291 --> 19:33.842
♪ THAT YOU CAN KEEP INSIDE YA ♪

19:33.843 --> 19:35.634
- JOE!
- AND DANI!

19:35.635 --> 19:37.005
- LEN!
- AND MEL!

19:37.006 --> 19:38.797
♪ ALL HOPE YOUR BIRTHDAY'S ♪

19:38.798 --> 19:41.059
♪ REALLY SWELL ♪

19:41.060 --> 19:43.352
♪ AND WHETHER OUR
SONG IS SHORT ♪

19:43.353 --> 19:46.765
♪ OR WHETHER IT IS LONG-O ♪

19:46.766 --> 19:49.978
♪ WE KNOW THAT ON
YOUR SPECIAL DAY ♪

19:49.979 --> 19:54.022
♪ YOU REALLY CAN'T GO WRONG-O ♪

19:54.023 --> 19:55.814
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT! MAYBE WE
SHOULD ADD SOME DANCE MOVES.

19:55.815 --> 19:58.817
YOU KNOW, LIKE A LITTLE
SINGLE LADIES STUFF.

19:58.818 --> 20:01.240
- MEL! -OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.
ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO.

20:01.241 --> 20:03.081
OKAY. HERE WE GO!

20:03.082 --> 20:04.783
- HEY! HAPPY BIRTHDAY, RYDER!
- All: HEY!

20:04.784 --> 20:08.497
HEY! WE WROTE YOU A SPECIAL
BIRTHDAY SONG. READY?

20:08.498 --> 20:10.709
Hold on, I'm about to go
to a midnight screening.

20:10.710 --> 20:13.252
So can you guys just, like,
email it to me or something?

20:13.253 --> 20:15.424
NO, NO, NO! THIS IS
VERY IMPORTANT TO YOU!

20:15.425 --> 20:18.258
Call me tomorrow.
Just not early.

20:22.181 --> 20:24.973
- WELL, THAT WAS UNDERWHELMING.
- YEAH.

20:24.974 --> 20:27.766
WELL, EVEN THOUGH WE DIDN'T GET
TO SING HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO RYDER,

20:27.767 --> 20:31.771
I... I STILL THINK WE CAN TAKE AWAY SOMETHING
KIND OF COOL FROM THIS WHOLE EXPERIENCE.

20:33.022 --> 20:35.524
THAT WAS AN AMAZING
INTERNET CONNECTION.

20:35.525 --> 20:39.908
DID YOU SEE HOW CLEAR THAT WAS? COME ON!
HUH? THAT WAS ALL ME.

20:39.909 --> 20:42.070
- ALL YOU?
- ISN'T YOUR ALLOWANCE COMING UP?

20:42.071 --> 20:44.324
- NO, IT WAS ALL YOU.
- HM...

20:46.786 --> 20:50.959
SO YOUR DAD MISSED YOUR SIXTEENTH
BIRTHDAY AND HE NEVER MADE IT UP TO YOU?

20:50.960 --> 20:53.251
- NOT EVEN A WORD OF APOLOGY?
- NOT A PEEP.

20:53.252 --> 20:54.463
HARSH.

20:54.464 --> 20:55.874
TELL ME ABOUT IT.
I MEAN, HE TRIED

20:55.875 --> 20:57.676
TO MAKE IT UP TO ME BY
BUYING ME A WHITE RABBIT,

20:57.677 --> 20:59.718
BUT I WAS LIKE, "TOO LITTLE
TOO LATE," YOU KNOW?

20:59.719 --> 21:01.380
AWWW. I WOULD HAVE
FORGIVEN MY DAD

21:01.381 --> 21:03.011
IF HE BOUGHT ME A
CUTE LITTLE BUNNY.

21:03.012 --> 21:04.883
OH, NO, A RABBIT CONVERTIBLE.

21:04.884 --> 21:08.597
YOU KNOW, TWO DOOR. STICK SHIFT.
LEATHER SEATS. THE WORKS.

21:08.598 --> 21:10.479
HE GAVE YOU A CAR?

21:10.480 --> 21:12.691
YEAH, BUT A CAR'S NOT
THE SAME AS LOVE.

21:12.692 --> 21:15.814
YEAH! YOU CAN'T DRIVE
LOVE TO COACHELLA!

21:15.815 --> 21:17.235
JOE, YOU KNOW WHAT
I'M TALKING ABOUT.

21:17.236 --> 21:19.898
IT'S WHAT'S FROM THE
HEART THAT'S IMPORTANT.

21:19.899 --> 21:21.861
HE GAVE YOU A CAR.

21:22.902 --> 21:24.904
OH, FORGET IT!
